body:
Bran Stark

I wish we had actually had an opportunity to grieve for Bran. The Three-Eyed Raven isn’t Bran at all, and I can’t help but think that the real Bran would be heartbroken to see that his body made it back to his home and family but his soul didn’t.

summary: Episode 8x04 was titled “The Last of the Stark’s”
body:
Episode 8x04 was titled “The Last of the Stark’s”

I may be reading too much into it but with Jon admitting he is not a Stark and never was a Stark to his sisters and now basically the world, Arya proclaiming she will not marry (and therefore probably won’t procreate children) and Sansa who could marry and have children but would take their fathers name because that’s how they roll in medieval times. And Bran, no emotion whatsoever, Stark won’t be fathering children. Like that’s it? They are the last of the Stark’s. After them, House Stark is gone.

:-(

summary: Simply going off a few scenes this season, i think D&D are doing a key-five, but they are different from Martin’s. Martin’s key...
body:
Simply going off a few scenes this season, i think D&D are doing a key-five, but they are different from Martin’s. Martin’s key five are: Jon, Dany, Tyrion, Arya, and Bran. I feel like D&D switched Bran out for Sansa which is…weird. They just focus on the other five so much more than Bran that it kinda feels like they switched them. 

I could, of course, be wrong.

let them learn to be happy in themselves and relearn who they are before making them settle down and start a family
summary: I don't know why GoT fans are acting like Arya and Sansa being single, unmarried, and childless at the end of the show would...
body:
I don’t know why GoT fans are acting like Arya and Sansa being single, unmarried, and childless at the end of the show would mean they’d NEVER settle down and get married and have families and that “the Stark line is over”? Like, they’re currently 18 and 20. They have their whole lives ahead of them. Their stories are only just beginning. They have all the time in the world.

And what about Bran? Sure, him ever having kids seems super unlikely now, but he’s only 17, anything could happen in the future!

As long as at least one of them survives the finale, and at this point I feel fairly confident they all will, the Stark line is not over. The pack survives.
